        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If exact shim measurement cannot be achieved, use available shims to approximate correct pinion
                    position.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position shims on carrier housing so oil return holes align properly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400761">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400761" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400761" filename="../figg14/G1400761.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Position Shims on Carrier Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be certain mounting surfaces and shims are free of dirt and nicks or leaks may occur and
                        pinion position can be affected.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pinion and pinion cage assembly into carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400762">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400762" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400762" filename="../figg14/G1400762.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Install Pinion and Pinion Cage Assembly into Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Studs can be used to assist in alignment.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten pinion cage to carrier bolts. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14007t_32.xml" xrefid="hl1400705">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1400705"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for proper fastener torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400763">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400763" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400763" filename="../figg14/G1400763.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Tighten Pinion Cage to Carrier Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
